        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 4:16PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Anthony Gap, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northeast El Paso, Chaparral, Anthony, and Anthony Gap.

This includes Interstate 10 in New Mexico near mile marker 164.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
